NC ACUPUNCTURE LICENSING BOARD
v.
NC BOARD OF PHYSICAL THERAPY EXAMINERS 380A17-1 Supreme Court of North Carolina. January 5, 2018 E. D. Gaskins, Jr., Attorney at Law, James M. Hash, Attorney at Law, Raleigh, Michael J. Tadych, Attorney at Law, Katherine Anne King, Attorney at Law, for N.C. Acupuncture Licensing Board. Stephen D. Feldman, Attorney at Law, James Michael Weiss, Attorney at Law, Troy D. Shelton, Attorney at Law, Raleigh, for N.C. Board of Physical Therapy Examiners.

The following order has been entered on the Consent Motion for Extension of Time to File Brief filed on the 4th of January 2018 by Defendant:

"Motion Allowed by order of the Court in conference, this the 5th of January 2018."

Defendant shall have up to and including the 16th day of February 2018 to file and serve his/her brief with this Court.
